# Copy to .env.local and set a strong password.
# This gates the /admin content editor.
ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me

# --- Optional: GitHub commit-back fallback for read-only hosts (Vercel) ---
# When the filesystem can't be written, the admin Save button commits
# content/site-content.json to the repo instead; the host then redeploys and
# the change goes live in ~1 minute. Locally these are NOT needed — the file
# is written directly.
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN  — fine-grained PAT, Contents → Read and write, ONLY this repo
# GITHUB_REPO   — "owner/repo", e.g. Denalix-Tech-LLC/Portfolio-Project
# GITHUB_BRANCH — optional, defaults to "main"
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_xxx
# GITHUB_REPO=Denalix-Tech-LLC/Portfolio-Project
# GITHUB_BRANCH=main
